    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-27T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-27T08:00:00-05:00" n="592"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d592">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5231/1035: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-27T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >September 27, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 27—10:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Request information as to accuracy statement in press to the effect that the
                    period during which Spain will enjoy the benefit of tariff reductions made other
                    countries under Trade Agreement Act<note n="21" xml:id="d592fn21">Approved June
                        12, 1934; 48 Stat. 943.</note> has been extended to December 31.<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d592fn22">By telegram No. 63, September 28, noon, the Department
                        informed the Ambassador that the duties proclaimed in connection with
                        Belgium, Haiti, and Sweden had been extended to Spain until January 1, 1936
                        (611.4231/1036a).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
